course_metadata.title: Digital twins and affective computing in built environments: an investigation of the characteristics, applications, and challenges

content_chunks.content: This course covers the integration of digital twins and affective computing to create smart, responsive built environments. Students will learn how digital models (digital twins) can optimize physical spaces in real-time, while affective computing adapts environments to human emotions for improved user experience. The course provides introduction to basics of Digital Twins and Affective Computing, Creating and managing digital models of buildings and cities, using emotional AI to design responsive spaces (lighting, HVAC, etc.), ethical considerations in data collection and system design.

Digital twin technology for responsive built environments and human-centered spaces - this course delivers expertise in creating virtual replicas of physical structures integrated with emotional AI systems for adaptive architecture. Students master digital modeling techniques, real-time data synchronization, and affective computing algorithms that enable buildings to respond to human emotions and behavior patterns. The curriculum covers sensor integration, emotional AI implementation, dynamic environmental controls, and ethical frameworks for emotion-sensitive design. Graduates emerge skilled in developing intelligent spaces that automatically adjust lighting, temperature, and spatial configurations based on occupant psychological states, revolutionizing how buildings interact with their inhabitants and creating truly responsive architectural experiences.
